Date: 26-08-2025 & 02-09-2025

Aim
To define an abstract Vehicle with a rental rate and abstract method.
To implement Car, Bike, Truck with specific cost calculation.
To compute and display rate and total cost for given days.
Algorithm
Read carRate, bikeRate, truckRate, and rentalDays (integers).
Define abstract class Vehicle with rate and calculateRentalCost(days).
Implement Car/Bike/Truck classes overriding cost method.
Instantiate each vehicle with the corresponding rate.
Print rental rate per day for each type.
Print total rental cost = rate × days for each type.
End program.
Program (Java)
import java.util.*;
abstract class Vehicle {
    protected int rate;
    public Vehicle(int rate){ this.rate = rate; }
    public abstract int calculateRentalCost(int days);
}
class Car extends Vehicle {
    public Car(int rate){ super(rate); }
    public int calculateRentalCost(int days){ return rate * days; }
}
class Bike extends Vehicle {
    public Bike(int rate){ super(rate); }
    public int calculateRentalCost(int days){ return rate * days; }
}
class Truck extends Vehicle {
    public Truck(int rate){ super(rate); }
    public int calculateRentalCost(int days){ return rate * days; }
}
public class VehicleRentalApp {
    public static void main(String[] args){
        Scanner sc = new Scanner(System.in);
        int carRate = Integer.parseInt(sc.nextLine().trim());
        int bikeRate = Integer.parseInt(sc.nextLine().trim());
        int truckRate = Integer.parseInt(sc.nextLine().trim());
        int days = Integer.parseInt(sc.nextLine().trim());
        Vehicle car = new Car(carRate);
        Vehicle bike = new Bike(bikeRate);
        Vehicle truck = new Truck(truckRate);
        System.out.println("Rental Rate: " + carRate + " per day");
        System.out.println("Total Rental Cost for Car: " + car.calculateRentalCost(days));
        System.out.println("Rental Rate: " + bikeRate + " per day");
        System.out.println("Total Rental Cost for Bike: " + bike.calculateRentalCost(days));
        System.out.println("Rental Rate: " + truckRate + " per day");
        System.out.println("Total Rental Cost for Truck: " + truck.calculateRentalCost(days));
        sc.close();
    }
}


Sample Output
Rental Rate: 1000 per day
Total Rental Cost for Car: 7000
Result
Implemented abstraction and concrete subclasses for vehicles.
Calculated total cost as rate × days for each type.
